RACE.FOOTNOTES: CENTAURUS was off slow, trailed the field early then moved between horses entering the turn, tipped out to three wide at the three furlong marker and kept on to engaged the leader at the top of the stretch and won going away. SILENCE'S NATION pressed the pace from the two path and took a narrow lead at the three furlong marker, inched away around the turn and was headed at the top of the stretch and gave way grudgingly but was a clear second. GUTFIELD tracked the leader from the three path but was no match for the top two. BIGPARTY NOWHISKEY raced wide throughout and passed tiring rivals. BARTSTER was off the pace while saving ground around the turn and never launched a bid. MAJOR TIMING was hustled to a pressured lead to the three furlong marker and gave way.
